Class Classifier

java.lang.Object
Classifier
Direct Known Subclasses:
ClassificationTree
public abstract class Classifier extends Object
This abstract class represents a Classifier, capable of assigning a label to a Classifiable input using probability

    • calculateAccuracy

      public Map<String,Double> calculateAccuracy(List<Classifiable> data, List<String> labels)
      Calculates the accuracy of this model on provided Lists of testing 'data' and corresponding 'labels'. The label for a datapoint at index 'i' within 'data' should be found at the same 'i' within 'labels'.
      Parameters:
      data - list of datapoints to try classifying
      labels - parallel list of expected labels
      Returns:
      an accuracy map, where keys are the labels encountered when classifying and values are the corresponding accuracies of each label
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if the the number of datapoints doesn't match the number of provided labels
      IllegalArgumentException - if any of the datapoints aren't able to be classified by this classifier
